<p>Hi <%= @user.first_name %>,</p>

<p>
  We detected <strong><%= @count %> failed sign-in attempts</strong> on your
  olubalance account from IP <strong><%= @ip %></strong> in the last
  <%= @window.inspect %>.
</p>

<p>
  If this was you (maybe a forgotten password), you can ignore this email — the
  rate limiter is doing its job and the attacker's IP is now throttled.
</p>

<p>
  If it wasn't you, your password is still safe (it wasn't guessed), but you may
  want to:
</p>

<ul>
  <li>Change your password as a precaution.</li>
  <li>Review your <a href="https://olubalance.com/security_events">security events page</a> for unusual successful logins.</li>
  <li>Confirm two-factor authentication is enabled at <a href="https://olubalance.com/two_factor_settings">/two_factor_settings</a>.</li>
</ul>

<p>— olubalance</p>
